Wallet.md — Web3Pay

Last Updated: September 10, 2025  
Purpose: Documenting supported wallets and integration methods  
Developer: Web3Pay Team  
Email: webpay603@gmail.com  

---

1. 🧭 Supported Wallets

Web3Pay supports the following wallets for sending, receiving, and storing digital assets:

- Pi Wallet (native integration)  
- Stellar Wallet  
- MetaMask (ERC20, BSC)  
- Trust Wallet  
- TronLink  

---

2. 🔗 Wallet Integration

- Users connect wallets via Web3 modal, QR code, or deep link  
- Wallet address is verified before any transaction  
- Biometric authentication is required before wallet actions  
- Wallets must support the selected network (e.g. ERC20, BEP20, Pi)

---

3. 🔐 Security Measures

- Web3Pay does not store private keys  
- Multi-signature support available for advanced users  
- Vault/HSM recommended for enterprise-level protection  
- All wallet actions are logged and timestamped for auditing  
- Failed wallet connections trigger alerts and retry options

---

4. ⚠️ Troubleshooting

- If wallet fails to connect:
  - Check network compatibility  
  - Ensure browser/app permissions are granted  
  - Verify wallet version and update if needed  
- For persistent issues, contact: webpay603@gmail.com

---

5. 📜 Legal Notice

Web3Pay does not store or manage user wallets.  
Users are responsible for securing their private keys and recovery phrases.  
Refer to Legal.md for full terms and conditions.
